The paper discusses the AGM theory of belief revision, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on probabilistic belief changes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR), where probabilistic models are often used. The paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) in its discussion of conditioning and constraining.
